Nakama ga irunda That's what your friends are there for
That’s what your friends are there for

12
00:00:36.850 --> 00:00:38.970
Y'know there's no point in fronting,

13
00:00:36.850 --> 00:00:42.900
Hora tsuyogari nante iranai itsudatte

14
00:00:38.970 --> 00:00:42.900
your crew will always have your back

15
00:00:43.270 --> 00:00:47.000
Yami ga hikisakou to shite mo Even in the face of utter darkness
Even in the face of utter darkness

16
00:00:47.230 --> 00:00:49.990
Hora Brave It Out C'mon BRAVE IT OUT Daijoubu sa We'll be alright
C’mon, BRAVE IT OUT We’ll be alright

17
00:00:50.290 --> 00:00:53.780
Uchiyaburu saikyou kizuna Together you know that we'll never lose a fight
Together you know that we’ll never lose a fight

18
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.770
Mugendai no chizu hiroge Open up the borderless map, then
Open up the borderless map, then

19
00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:59.630
Hateshinai ano basho he Head for that unknown edge of the ocean
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

20
00:00:59.930 --> 00:01:04.210
Fumidase yuuki no ippo All great journeys start with a single step
All great journeys starts with a single step

21
00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:05.220
Dreamin' On DREAMIN' ON
DREAMIN’ ON

22
00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:08.000
Mugendai no chizu hiroge Open up the borderless map, then
Open up the borderless map, then

23
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.740
Chikaiatsumeta hata Raise up the flag we swore to defend
Raise the flag we swore to defend

24
00:01:10.890 --> 00:01:13.630
Tatakai tsudzukete yuku We'll never stop until we've reached the top
We’ll never stop until we’ve reached the top

25
00:01:13.700 --> 00:01:18.100
Jibun jishin tsuranuke Just be true to yourself until the end
Just be true to yourself until the end

26
00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:22.940
Tsukamitoru Dreamin' On Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON
Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON

27
00:01:38.490 --> 00:01:41.040
Roger's Adventure

28
00:01:46.170 --> 00:01:47.500
Ouch!

29
00:01:48.380 --> 00:01:49.460
So cold!

30
00:01:54.720 --> 00:01:59.520
With the help of Gan Fall, the god above
the clouds, we reached the sea safely.

31
00:01:59.530 --> 00:02:00.430
The North Pole!

32
00:02:00.430 --> 00:02:01.310
No, the South Pole!

33
00:02:01.310 --> 00:02:02.770
You won't budge, huh?!

34
00:02:02.770 --> 00:02:05.810
You got it! And I'll keep
sayin' it cause I'm right!

35
00:02:05.810 --> 00:02:06.980
Knock it off!

36
00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:10.940
All you two ever do is fight!

37
00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:15.990
Our destination is none other than
the final island on the Grand Line!

38
00:02:15.990 --> 00:02:20.620
But to get there, we need copies
of all four lode poneglyphs.

39
00:02:20.620 --> 00:02:22.750
Like that stone we found on the sky island?

40
00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:25.000
There is one in Wano.

41
00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.840
Mrowr Mokomo Dukedom has one, too.

42
00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:31.300
Your homelands both have stones like that?!

43
00:02:31.300 --> 00:02:33.300
Unlike the one on the sky island...

44
00:02:33.300 --> 00:02:34.470
– ...it's red!
– ...it's red!

45
00:02:34.470 --> 00:02:36.300
Those are the ones I want the most!

46
00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:37.970
Why didn't you say something?!

47
00:02:37.970 --> 00:02:40.140
So we'll have two out of four!

48
00:02:40.140 --> 00:02:45.480
No, we also snatched a copy
of Linlin's lode poneglyph.

49
00:02:45.480 --> 00:02:49.020
And I've got a hunch where the last one is.

50
00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:50.570
Nice going, Roger!

51
00:02:50.570 --> 00:02:52.740
Yeah, I can't believe our luck!

52
00:02:52.740 --> 00:02:54.860
We'll really have all four!

53
00:02:55.950 --> 00:03:00.740
Sorry to spoil the celebration,
but something's wrong with the ship.

54
00:03:00.740 --> 00:03:01.540
What?

55
00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:05.540
I'm no shipwright, so I can't tell what's busted.

56
00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:07.920
Well then, I know just the place!

57
00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:08.880
Where?

58
00:03:08.880 --> 00:03:11.460
The City of Water, Water Seven!

59
00:03:11.460 --> 00:03:12.840
The City of Water?

60
00:03:12.840 --> 00:03:14.380
Sounds romantic!

61
00:03:14.380 --> 00:03:16.590
Alright men, let's go!

62
00:03:16.590 --> 00:03:18.510
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

63
00:03:19.010 --> 00:03:25.480
Thus, we headed to
the shipbuilding town for repairs.

64
00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:36.280
Scrap Island
Water Seven

65
00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:42.790
Tom
(The Shipwright
Who Built Roger's Ship)

66
00:03:40.450 --> 00:03:42.790
It's damn good to see you, Roger!

67
00:03:42.790 --> 00:03:44.040
Tom!

68
00:03:44.450 --> 00:03:45.960
– Tom!
– Tom!

69
00:03:46.290 --> 00:03:47.670
Hey, Mr. Tom!

70
00:03:50.590 --> 00:03:52.710
It's been a while, guys!

71
00:03:52.710 --> 00:03:54.710
Yeah, I missed you!

72
00:03:56.170 --> 00:03:57.930
You finish that train yet?

73
00:03:57.930 --> 00:03:59.930
You mean the sea train?!

74
00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:02.810
No way! It's still in the design phase!

75
00:04:08.100 --> 00:04:11.770
Kokoro
A Beautiful Secretary
Tom's Workers

76
00:04:09.310 --> 00:04:11.770
You guys are as noisy as ever!

77
00:04:18.910 --> 00:04:21.070
Are you an orphan?!

78
00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:23.490
Do you want me to introduce
you to our captain?

79
00:04:24.540 --> 00:04:26.120
You guys are pirates, right?

80
00:04:26.120 --> 00:04:27.330
What of it?

81
00:04:27.660 --> 00:04:29.170
Then, no way.

82
00:04:29.170 --> 00:04:31.540
I just got ditched by pirates.

83
00:04:31.540 --> 00:04:32.510
Ditched?!

84
00:04:34.630 --> 00:04:36.130
Bad timing!

85
00:04:40.800 --> 00:04:44.760
♪ Gather up all of the crew! ♪
♪ Time to ship out Binks' brew! ♪

86
00:04:44.760 --> 00:04:49.390
♪ Pirates, we tirelessly ♪
♪ are challenging the sea! ♪

87
00:04:49.390 --> 00:04:53.520
♪ Somewhere in the endless sky, ♪
♪ stormy winds are blowing by! ♪

88
00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:57.530
♪ Waves are dancing, evening comes, ♪
♪ it's time to sound the drums! ♪

89
00:04:57.530 --> 00:05:01.910
♪ Steady men, and never fear, ♪
♪ future skies are always clear! ♪

90
00:04:57.570 --> 00:05:01.910
Tequila Wolf
A Country on a Bridge

91
00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:06.490
♪ Pound your feet, clap your hands ♪
♪ till sunny days return! ♪

92
00:05:13.670 --> 00:05:17.840
Sabaody Archipelago

93
00:05:20.550 --> 00:05:22.300
Let's set sail!

94
00:05:30.020 --> 00:05:31.890
Fishman Island, huh?

95
00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:35.150
I went there once with Whitekichi!

96
00:05:35.150 --> 00:05:37.230
Don't drop your guard!

97
00:05:37.230 --> 00:05:40.820
No matter how many times you go,
your chances of dying won't change!

98
00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:45.780
Rayleigh! Did you hear that?

99
00:05:45.780 --> 00:05:47.330
What are you talking about?

100
00:05:47.330 --> 00:05:49.160
There's nothing to hear this deep.

101
00:05:49.160 --> 00:05:51.330
No, I can hear it, too.

102
00:05:51.330 --> 00:05:53.210
You, too, Oden?

103
00:05:54.460 --> 00:05:58.300
Who's talking this deep in the water?!

104
00:06:01.840 --> 00:06:04.640
Toki! That's Fishman Island!

105
00:06:04.640 --> 00:06:05.970
How curious...

106
00:06:05.970 --> 00:06:09.220
It seems like the whole island is in a bubble...

107
00:06:09.930 --> 00:06:10.860
Those are...

108
00:06:10.850 --> 00:06:12.020
...fishmen!

109
00:06:12.020 --> 00:06:13.520
They have surrounded us!

110
00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:16.440
State your business, surface dwellers!

111
00:06:17.730 --> 00:06:19.690
Whoa, wait, wait. Look closer!

112
00:06:19.690 --> 00:06:21.530
It's me! Roger!

113
00:06:21.530 --> 00:06:23.150
Great Knight Neptune!

114
00:06:23.530 --> 00:06:24.910
Roger?

115
00:06:25.910 --> 00:06:27.870
Oh, it all makes sense!

116
00:06:27.870 --> 00:06:29.910
So you guys are gonna do it!

117
00:06:30.410 --> 00:06:37.630
Mermaid Cove
Ryugu Kingdom

118
00:06:30.910 --> 00:06:33.210
We're not up to any trouble!

119
00:06:33.210 --> 00:06:35.460
Come on, why are you scared of a prophecy?

120
00:06:35.460 --> 00:06:37.630
You're better than that!

121
00:06:38.250 --> 00:06:43.220
It foretold someone breaking
the gates of Fishman Island soon!

122
00:06:43.220 --> 00:06:46.970
And now that you've arrived, it all points to...

123
00:06:49.970 --> 00:06:52.140
King Neptune, it's been broken!

124
00:06:52.140 --> 00:06:54.190
The sea kings chewed up the gate!

125
00:06:54.190 --> 00:06:57.520
What?! But they're such gentle creatures!

126
00:06:57.520 --> 00:06:58.860
It can't be true!

127
00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:00.320
It came true...

128
00:07:01.940 --> 00:07:03.820
The outer bubble's been breached!

129
00:07:03.820 --> 00:07:06.320
Seal it immediately! Begin emergency repairs!

130
00:07:06.660 --> 00:07:08.370
We couldn't prevent it.

131
00:07:08.370 --> 00:07:10.990
See?! It wasn't us!

132
00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:18.880
Sharley
Prophet Girl
(Three Years Old)
The sea kings are growing restless because
they're waiting for the Mermaid Princess to be born.

133
00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:21.800
The Mermaid Princess?!
That's another prophecy.

134
00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:23.920
So the king will have a baby?!

135
00:07:23.920 --> 00:07:26.010
We have to celebrate!

136
00:07:26.010 --> 00:07:27.260
Wait, wait!

137
00:07:27.260 --> 00:07:29.760
I'm not even married yet!

138
00:07:29.760 --> 00:07:33.270
I've only been king for a few months!

139
00:07:33.270 --> 00:07:35.060
But King Neptune!

140
00:07:35.430 --> 00:07:40.560
She even divined the day
that the former king would die!

141
00:07:42.480 --> 00:07:44.610
She also predicted that seductive...

142
00:07:44.610 --> 00:07:50.120
I mean, seditious mermaid Otohime's
political demonstration the other day!

143
00:07:50.780 --> 00:07:53.700
I-It's not like it brought me any comfort!

144
00:07:53.700 --> 00:08:01.460
Deepwater Grove
Ryugu Kingdom

145
00:07:57.160 --> 00:08:01.460
These days, the whole country
is swayed by that girl's prophecies...

146
00:08:01.790 --> 00:08:06.090
We didn't come to hear
your life story, Neptune.

147
00:08:06.090 --> 00:08:07.970
Ah, that's right.

148
00:08:09.260 --> 00:08:10.510
Any luck, Oden?

149
00:08:10.510 --> 00:08:11.350
Well...

150
00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:14.970
There are two, so I thought
we could get a lot of information,

151
00:08:14.970 --> 00:08:17.810
but one of them seems mostly irrelevant.

152
00:08:17.810 --> 00:08:21.190
It is a letter of apology
from someone named Joyboy.

153
00:08:21.190 --> 00:08:24.400
Unbelievable! He really can read the script!

154
00:08:24.400 --> 00:08:28.320
More importantly, do you have
a weapon capable of controlling sea kings?

155
00:08:28.320 --> 00:08:29.700
A weapon?!

156
00:08:29.700 --> 00:08:33.660
The stone on the sky island said it's here.

157
00:08:34.160 --> 00:08:36.950
An ancient weapon
bearing the name of a god...

158
00:08:38.290 --> 00:08:40.420
"Poseidon."

159
00:08:41.790 --> 00:08:43.420
To tell you the truth...

160
00:08:44.050 --> 00:08:49.010
I felt a slight chill when I heard
Sharley's prophecy earlier.

161
00:08:50.970 --> 00:08:53.720
Once every few centuries in this country,

162
00:08:53.720 --> 00:08:57.810
a mermaid who can talk
to the sea kings is born.

163
00:09:00.440 --> 00:09:03.020
Could that mermaid really be...

164
00:09:03.020 --> 00:09:07.530
So your daughter will become the weapon
that destroys the world someday?

165
00:09:08.190 --> 00:09:10.490
It's just a prophecy!

166
00:09:10.490 --> 00:09:14.870
And even if it's called an ancient weapon,
it doesn't have to be used as one!

167
00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:18.330
I never would've guessed
that Poseidon was a mermaid!

168
00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:28.800
Hey, Sharley, when will
the Mermaid Princess be born?

169
00:09:35.180 --> 00:09:36.390
Ten!

170
00:09:36.530 --> 00:09:37.390
Huh?

171
00:09:37.390 --> 00:09:39.140
So ten years from now...

172
00:09:39.140 --> 00:09:42.940
But, Roger, I can't believe
you're interested in such a weapon!

173
00:09:42.940 --> 00:09:44.440
I misjudged you!

174
00:09:44.440 --> 00:09:52.240
Actually, Neptune, we're after the vast treasure
left behind by the people who called it a weapon!

175
00:09:53.660 --> 00:09:55.160
Feel better?

176
00:09:55.160 --> 00:10:00.040
We won't be coming back
to kidnap your hairy daughter!

177
00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:02.160
She won't be hairy!

178
00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:18.930
♪ Gather up all of the crew! ♪
♪ Time to ship out Binks' brew! ♪

179
00:10:18.930 --> 00:10:22.890
♪ Wave goodbye, don't you cry, ♪
♪ our memories remain. ♪

180
00:10:23.390 --> 00:10:27.730
♪ Days are but a passing dream, ♪
♪ everlasting though they seem. ♪

181
00:10:27.730 --> 00:10:31.900
♪ Beneath the moon we'll meet again, ♪
♪ the wind's our lullaby! ♪

182
00:10:52.260 --> 00:10:54.090
In 

the Seas

Near Wano

183
00:10:57.470 --> 00:10:58.760
Hey, Oden!

184
00:10:59.470 --> 00:11:01.100
What is wrong, Redtaro?

185
00:11:01.100 --> 00:11:02.770
Toki collapsed!

186
00:11:02.770 --> 00:11:04.520
What?!

187
00:11:11.650 --> 00:11:12.480
Toki!

188
00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:14.110
Do not worry!

189
00:11:14.110 --> 00:11:15.700
I am here with you!

190
00:11:19.740 --> 00:11:21.580
Oden...

191
00:11:21.580 --> 00:11:25.120
Toki has been following you
and traveling the world,

192
00:11:25.120 --> 00:11:28.290
but her original destination was Wano.

193
00:11:28.290 --> 00:11:32.420
As Wano draws nearer,
she's started to wear down,

194
00:11:32.420 --> 00:11:35.630
and the fatigue of the long journey has hit her.

195
00:11:35.630 --> 00:11:39.140
If she continues, she could die.

196
00:11:39.140 --> 00:11:43.850
She should disembark at Wano
and bring her journey to a close.

197
00:11:43.850 --> 00:11:47.520
Kin'emon and the others
don't know Lady Toki well.

198
00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:50.230
So Inuarashi and I will accompany her.

199
00:11:50.230 --> 00:11:54.570
The place is unfamiliar to them,
so I'm sure they'll feel lonely.

200
00:11:54.900 --> 00:11:58.240
Leave Lady Toki in our care.

201
00:11:58.240 --> 00:12:00.070
There is no way that I will just–

202
00:12:02.200 --> 00:12:03.200
Toki?

203
00:12:07.040 --> 00:12:09.460
You have to go, Oden!

204
00:12:10.210 --> 00:12:11.960
What are you saying?!

205
00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:14.880
If you quit over a little thing like this...

206
00:12:15.380 --> 00:12:16.300
I...

207
00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:20.800
will dissolve our marriage!

208
00:12:33.270 --> 00:12:40.530
We have eagerly awaited the day
you would return, Lord Oden!

209
00:12:41.120 --> 00:12:45.950
We have endeavored to look after
Kuri in your absence, however...

210
00:12:45.950 --> 00:12:48.540
Not just Kuri, but all of Wano is–

211
00:12:48.540 --> 00:12:49.290
Wait!

212
00:12:49.290 --> 00:12:50.000
– Huh?
– Huh?

213
00:12:50.370 --> 00:12:53.840
If you truly care about Oden...

214
00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:55.550
Please!

215
00:12:55.550 --> 00:12:57.340
Let him go!

216
00:12:57.920 --> 00:12:59.130
I...

217
00:13:00.590 --> 00:13:04.050
I will be away for a little longer.

218
00:13:11.650 --> 00:13:17.190
Even as I turned away, I could tell
that something about Wano had changed.

219
00:13:19.070 --> 00:13:23.820
I knew that should I look back,
I would never resume my voyage.

220
00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:28.410
– Damn you, Lord Oden!
– Damn you, Lord Oden!

221
00:13:28.410 --> 00:13:30.870
– You deadbeat!
– You deadbeat!

222
00:13:32.370 --> 00:13:38.840
I quickly made a rubbing of the poneglyph
in Wano and returned to the sea.

223
00:13:38.840 --> 00:13:43.720
It was my first time home in four years,
but I only stayed for a few hours.

224
00:13:50.310 --> 00:13:51.940
You deadbeat.

225
00:13:51.940 --> 00:13:54.520
How about reading the script yourself then?!

226
00:13:56.520 --> 00:13:59.440
I'm truly sorry, Oden.

227
00:14:04.490 --> 00:14:10.580
Next, we headed to the Mokomo Dukedom,
Nekomamushi and Inuarashi's homeland.

228
00:14:10.580 --> 00:14:13.790
It was said to be on the back of an elephant.

229
00:14:14.170 --> 00:14:18.170
I was told that we could only get
to Zou with this vivre card.

230
00:14:22.420 --> 00:14:25.010
You are indeed correct that this is no island!

231
00:14:25.010 --> 00:14:26.260
An elephant?!

232
00:14:32.310 --> 00:14:34.440
Whose voice is this?

233
00:14:34.440 --> 00:14:37.230
Oden, what's the matter?

234
00:14:37.230 --> 00:14:42.070
Well, I suppose it is nothing,
but I have this peculiar feeling...

235
00:14:42.070 --> 00:14:46.030
Mokomo Dukedom

236
00:14:48.830 --> 00:14:53.960
Duke Genghis Baan
Mokomo Dukedom

237
00:14:50.620 --> 00:14:53.960
A letter from Inuarashi and Nekomamushi!

238
00:14:53.960 --> 00:14:55.870
So they're still alive!

239
00:14:55.870 --> 00:14:57.880
Those rapscallions...!

240
00:14:58.750 --> 00:15:01.630
Their disappearance caused
quite the commotion!

241
00:15:01.630 --> 00:15:04.550
Thank you for putting our minds at ease.

242
00:15:11.810 --> 00:15:14.060
I feel uneasy...

243
00:15:14.060 --> 00:15:17.150
Are you okay, Oden?
That doesn't sound like you.

244
00:15:17.150 --> 00:15:19.190
I know how you feel, Oden.

245
00:15:19.190 --> 00:15:20.520
You, too, Captain Roger?!

246
00:15:20.940 --> 00:15:26.240
It kind of feels like I'm being
watched by something really big...

247
00:15:39.920 --> 00:15:41.130
Here it is!

248
00:15:41.130 --> 00:15:43.300
The last lode poneglyph!

249
00:15:43.300 --> 00:15:45.880
The Kozuki family crest!

250
00:15:45.880 --> 00:15:49.800
So we truly share a brotherly
bond with the minks!

251
00:15:55.640 --> 00:15:58.480
I'm beggin' you, take me along!

252
00:15:58.480 --> 00:16:02.400
Kid, you still have to wait.

253
00:16:02.860 --> 00:16:04.230
Listen!

254
00:16:04.740 --> 00:16:08.110
Everyone gets their own turn.

255
00:16:08.950 --> 00:16:10.410
My own turn?!

256
00:16:10.410 --> 00:16:13.450
When the time comes, I'm counting on you.

257
00:16:15.870 --> 00:16:17.120
Okay!

258
00:16:17.120 --> 00:16:18.670
I'll help you for sure!

259
00:16:19.330 --> 00:16:21.710
Goodbye, Pedro.

260
00:16:25.760 --> 00:16:31.220
We found the four lode poneglyphs
and several parts of the Rio Poneglyph.

261
00:16:31.220 --> 00:16:34.810
Our adventure's conclusion is approaching.

262
00:16:39.140 --> 00:16:40.650
In a Port Town

263
00:16:43.690 --> 00:16:45.820
Captain, are you okay?!

264
00:16:53.530 --> 00:16:56.200
Have you figured out where the final island is?

265
00:16:56.200 --> 00:16:58.210
Yes, we have.

266
00:16:58.210 --> 00:16:59.920
When should we leave?

267
00:17:00.870 --> 00:17:02.580
Immediately!

268
00:17:02.580 --> 00:17:03.630
– Okay!
– Okay!

269
00:17:03.630 --> 00:17:06.340
Alright, let's go!

270
00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:19.020
For better or for worse, the apprentice
Buggyjiro suddenly took ill with a fever

271
00:17:19.430 --> 00:17:22.850
and had to withdraw from the final voyage.

272
00:17:22.850 --> 00:17:26.730
Only a damn kid would catch a cold
right before a great adventure.

273
00:17:26.730 --> 00:17:30.070
Shut up! I said I'm better now!

274
00:17:30.490 --> 00:17:34.200
Your face is red, and you're
burning up. Give it a rest.

275
00:17:34.200 --> 00:17:36.870
Who'd you say has a big, red nose?!

276
00:17:36.870 --> 00:17:38.120
Clean out your ears!

277
00:17:38.120 --> 00:17:39.500
Go on!

278
00:17:39.500 --> 00:17:40.620
Have at it!

279
00:17:40.620 --> 00:17:43.500
Roger! Oden! Don't encourage them!

280
00:17:45.590 --> 00:17:48.170
Flashy treasure's waiting for me!

281
00:17:48.170 --> 00:17:49.880
Don't push yourself, idiot!

282
00:17:49.880 --> 00:17:51.760
I'm coming, too!

283
00:17:54.890 --> 00:17:58.520
Captain, take me with you!

284
00:18:00.730 --> 00:18:03.350
You're like a little monster, huh?

285
00:18:03.730 --> 00:18:05.810
Although they bicker constantly,

286
00:18:05.810 --> 00:18:09.360
in the end, Redtaro took it
upon himself to look after him.

287
00:18:11.070 --> 00:18:14.620
I cannot tell if they are close
friends or bitter rivals.

288
00:18:17.990 --> 00:18:21.330
Take me with you...

289
00:18:22.830 --> 00:18:27.880
While Buggyjiro is very upset over this,
are are fine with this outcome, Redtaro?

290
00:18:27.880 --> 00:18:29.880
Oden. Captain.

291
00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:34.720
If we wanna go there, 
we'll take our own ships someday!

292
00:18:57.570 --> 00:19:01.790
♪ Gather up all of the crew! ♪
♪ Time to ship out Binks' brew! ♪

293
00:19:01.790 --> 00:19:06.380
♪ Pirates, we tirelessly ♪
♪ are challenging the sea! ♪

294
00:19:06.380 --> 00:19:10.420
♪ With the waves to rest our heads, ♪
♪ ships beneath us as our beds! ♪

295
00:19:10.420 --> 00:19:14.760
♪ Hoisted high upon the mast ♪
♪ our Jolly Roger flies! ♪

296
00:19:11.130 --> 00:19:13.840
The Roger Pirates finally did it!

297
00:19:13.840 --> 00:19:18.800
That pirate, Roger, is the first man
in history to circumnavigate the world!

298
00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:18.800
♪ Somewhere in the endless sky, ♪
♪ stormy winds are blowing by! ♪

299
00:19:18.800 --> 00:19:23.310
♪ Waves are dancing, evening comes, ♪
♪ it's time to sound the drums! ♪

300
00:19:18.800 --> 00:19:21.850
Someone's finally conquered the sea!

301
00:19:21.850 --> 00:19:24.140
He's truly the king of the sea!

302
00:19:23.310 --> 00:19:27.560
♪ Steady men, and never fear, ♪
♪ future skies are always clear! ♪

303
00:19:25.060 --> 00:19:27.310
The King of the Pirates!

304
00:19:27.560 --> 00:19:31.860
♪ Pound your feet, clap your hands ♪
♪ till sunny days return! ♪

